# Testing bad comparisons of durations and related error messages

```catala-metadata
declaration structure St:
  data a content integer
  data b content optional of duration

declaration enumeration E:
  -- A
  -- S content St

declaration scope S1:
  output o content boolean
declaration scope S2:
  output o content boolean
declaration scope S3:
  output o content boolean
declaration scope S4:
  output o content boolean

scope S1:
  definition o equals A > A
scope S2:
  definition o equals
    S content St { -- a: 12 -- b: Absent } >=
    S content St { -- a: 12 -- b: Absent }
scope S3:
  definition o equals
    S content St { -- a: 12 -- b: Present content (3 year + 2 month) } >=
    S content St { -- a: 12 -- b: Present content 3 year }
scope S4:
  definition o equals
    S content St { -- a: 12 -- b: Present content (3 year + 2 month + 1 day) } >=
    S content St { -- a: 12 -- b: Present content 3 year }
```

```catala-test-cli
$ catala test-scope S1
┌─[RESULT]─ S1 ─
│ o = false
└─
```
```catala-test-cli
$ catala test-scope S2
┌─[RESULT]─ S2 ─
│ o = true
└─
```
```catala-test-cli
$ catala test-scope S3
┌─[RESULT]─ S3 ─
│ o = true
└─
```
```catala-test-cli
$ catala test-scope S4
┌─[ERROR]─
│
│  During evaluation: ambiguous comparison between durations in different
│  units (e.g. months vs. days).
│
├─➤ tests/introspection/bad/durations.catala_en:33.80-33.82:
│    │
│ 33 │     S content St { -- a: 12 -- b: Present content (3 year + 2 month + 1 day) } >=
│    │                                                                                ‾‾
└─ Testing bad comparisons of durations and related error messages
#return code 123#
```
